-- SHADOW-SEMANTICS cell D18: FIXED (issue #410 headline repro), was BUILD_CRASH.
--
-- Identical to d17 but WITHOUT the `List Int` annotation.  The emitter arity lie
-- d17 pins was already fixed; d18 pinned a SEPARATE, upstream bug now also closed.
--
-- Root cause (contra the old note, which blamed the "route stamped without being
-- resolved against the inferred type"): the EMIT path typed the bare value-position
-- shadow `size` as the permissive METHOD scheme (`a -> a -> Int`), NOT the standalone
-- (`Int -> Int`), because maybeStandaloneValueMono keys on the BARE name and the mangler
-- had renamed the standalone funDef to `<mid>__size`.  So `map size [1,2,3]` inferred
-- element type `Int -> Int` (a function), and `println`'s `Display (List (Int -> Int))`
-- correctly stamped a NULL element dict (there is no Display for a function): the
-- `@mdk_dc_N = [2 x i64] [<List-display tag>, i64 0]` was faithful to a WRONG type.  `run`
-- was correct ([2, 3, 4]) because eval follows the RLocal route this same call stamped.
--
-- Fix: maybeStandaloneValueMonoEmit (compiler/types/typecheck.mdk) — inferMethodAt now
-- recovers the post-mangle shadow from the occurrence's RLocal route sym and pins the
-- standalone scheme, so the element grounds to Int BEFORE resolveDictApps.  Now ALL_EXACT
-- [2, 3, 4] on check/run/build.  Its importer twin is i6b (#669).
interface Sizeable a where
  size : a -> a -> Int

data Box = Box Int

impl Sizeable Box where
  size (Box a) (Box b) = a + b

size : Int -> Int
size n = n + 1

main = println (map size [1, 2, 3])
